<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="divide-v">divide <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /dɪ'vaɪd/    美 /dɪ'vaɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>划分；分割；分配；分开：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The fence <strong>divides</strong> the garden <strong>into</strong> two.
篱笆把花园隔成两半。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>As the work can be <strong>divided among</strong> several people, it can be done efficiently.
因为工作可以由几个人共同分担，所以可以做得很有效率。</p><footer>2008 浙江</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Nothing is particularly hard if you divide it into small jobs.
如果化整为零，任何事情都不会特别困难。</p><footer>—亨利·福特</footer></div>

<h3 id="divide-separate">辨析 divide, separate</h3>
<p>二者均可表示“分开”。<br />
<strong>divide</strong> 通常指把整体分为若干部分，其后常接介词 into。
<strong>separate</strong> 通常指把原来连在一起或靠近的东西分隔开来，其后常接介词 from。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We’d better <strong>separate</strong> the good ones <strong>from</strong> the bad ones.
我们最好把好的和坏的分开。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She doesn’t want to be <strong>separated from</strong> him.
她不想和他分开。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(被) 除 (尽)；把…作除数：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Ten <strong>divided by</strong> two equals five.
10除以2等于5。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>8 <strong>divides into</strong> 64.
64可以用8整除。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>使产生分歧：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We can achieve a lot when we learn to let our differences unite, rather than divide us.
当我们学会让差异将我们团结起来而不是彼此对立，我们就能收获颇丰。</p><footer>2016 浙江</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>There is much work to do, so we’ll have to <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (分) it between us.  （2008 陕西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. divide  </p></div>